<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936866>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Arcotheres vicajii (Chhapgar, 1957) comb. nov.. A–I, ovigerous female (CW 8.2 mm, CL 6.9 mm) (ZRC 2018.0768), India; J, K, non-ovigerous female (CW 8.0 mm, CL 6.7 mm) (ZRC 2018.0768), India; L, juvenile female (CW 4.0 mm, CL 3.6 mm) (ZRC 2018.0769), India. A, L, left MXP3 (setae not drawn); B, left chela and carpus; C–F, left P2–P5, respectively (P3 carpus, propodus and dactylus missing); G–I, right P2, P4 and P5, respectively; J, left P3; K, right P3 Scales = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3936866/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936862>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Arcotheres vicajii (Chhapgar, 1957) comb. nov., A–I, female (CW 8.6 mm, CL 7.7 mm) (LFSC.ZRC-115), Mumbai, India; J–M, holotype, male (CW 3.7 mm, CL 3.7 mm) (ZSI-C3361/1), Mumbai, India. A–D, left P2–P5, respectively; E–H, right P2–P5, respectively; I, right P5 dactylus tip; J–M,right P2–P5, respectively. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3936862/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936860>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Arcotheres vicajii (Chhapgar, 1957) comb. nov., holotype, male (CW 3.7 mm, CL 3.7 mm) (ZSI-C3361/1), Mumbai, India.A, carapace; B, pleon; C, right chela outer view D, left G1; E, left G2. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3936860/files/figure.png" ;
