<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936868>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Arcotheres vicajii (Chhapgar, 1957) comb. nov., male (CW 4.5 mm, CL 4.2 mm) (ZRC 2018.0768), India. A, left MXP3 (setae not drawn); B, left chela and carpus; C–F, right P2–P5, respectively; G, male pleon; H, left G1 (dorsal view); I, left G1 (ventral view); J, left G2 with exopod. Scales = 0.5 mm." ;
